00:57:02,557 --> 00:57:06,112
They're giving you Showman
of the Year tomorrow night.

1066
00:57:06,146 --> 00:57:06,837
- So?

1067
00:57:06,871 --> 00:57:08,494
They'll name me it every year.

1068
00:57:08,528 --> 00:57:10,910
- 1200 people at the Waldorf Astoria.

1069
00:57:10,944 --> 00:57:11,980
- Am I wrong, doc?

1070
00:57:12,014 --> 00:57:14,500
- I'd say there's gonna
be one less than 1200

1071
00:57:14,534 --> 00:57:17,123
at the Waldorf tomorrow night.

1072
00:57:18,296 --> 00:57:21,299
- Hey!
[laughing]

1073
00:57:21,334 --> 00:57:23,854
Hi you guys, Mommy's real sick now.

1074
00:57:23,888 --> 00:57:24,924
[laughing]

1075
00:57:24,958 --> 00:57:26,443
[children shouting]

1076
00:57:26,477 --> 00:57:27,547
- Let's take the puppies,

1077
00:57:27,582 --> 00:57:29,998
and we'll go rustle up some cookies, huh?

1078
00:57:30,032 --> 00:57:31,068
- Say bye to Mommy.

1079
00:57:31,102 --> 00:57:33,173
- I love you, I love you.

1080
00:57:44,737 --> 00:57:47,464
- This is a good angle.

1081
00:57:47,498 --> 00:57:49,845
- For what, a picture about a corpse?

1082
00:57:49,880 --> 00:57:52,227
- I'm gonna use it in my next picture.

1083
00:57:52,261 --> 00:57:53,228
- Kiss me.

1084
00:57:53,262 --> 00:57:55,541
- I already did, won't change my mind.

1085
00:57:55,575 --> 00:57:58,613
- Then kiss me for the hell of it.

1086
00:58:01,374 --> 00:58:04,032
- Oh God, you make me so happy.

1087
00:58:06,690 --> 00:58:08,864
[thunder booming]

1088
00:58:08,899 --> 00:58:09,555
- Oh, Mike.

1089
00:58:09,589 --> 00:58:10,763
- Don't you worry, sweetie.

1090
00:58:10,797 --> 00:58:13,006
I can fly above any storm.

1091
00:58:13,041 --> 00:58:14,663
I married you, didn't I?

1092
00:58:14,698 --> 00:58:16,458
I'll call you from Tulsa.

1093
00:58:16,493 --> 00:58:17,459
- What time?

1094
00:58:17,494 --> 00:58:18,322
- Three AM sharp.

1095
00:58:18,356 --> 00:58:19,185
- Don't forget.

1096
00:58:19,219 --> 00:58:20,289
- Yes, Mummy.

1097
00:58:27,020 --> 00:58:28,953
Oh, forgot something!

1098
00:58:28,988 --> 00:58:31,197
[laughing]

1099
00:58:34,890 --> 00:58:35,546
I love you.

1100
00:58:35,581 --> 00:58:36,823
- I love you.

1101
00:58:43,934 --> 00:58:45,970
[thunder booming]

1102
00:58:46,005 --> 00:58:49,077
[suspenseful music]

1103
00:59:03,056 --> 00:59:04,023
Doctor?

1104
00:59:04,057 --> 00:59:06,819
This isn't a medical
emergency or anything.

1105
00:59:06,853 --> 00:59:09,131
- Elizabeth, what's wrong?

1106
00:59:10,581 --> 00:59:12,514
- It's after three.

1107
00:59:12,549 --> 00:59:13,791
- Tell me.

1108
00:59:13,826 --> 00:59:18,727
- Mike was supposed to
call from Tulsa, by three.

1109
00:59:18,762 --> 00:59:20,764
- Mike can take care of himself.

1110
00:59:20,798 --> 00:59:22,628
- I have this feeling.

1111
00:59:22,662 --> 00:59:25,527
- I can hear you smoking.

1112
00:59:25,562 --> 00:59:26,597
- I'm not.

1113
00:59:27,356 --> 00:59:29,496
- Liz, you're sick.

1114
00:59:29,531 --> 00:59:30,705
Go to sleep.

1115
00:59:31,809 --> 00:59:33,570
- When Mike calls.

1116
01:00:12,885 --> 01:00:13,748
No, no!

1117
01:00:15,646 --> 01:00:17,890
[crying]

1118
01:00:22,377 --> 01:00:25,276
- I'm sorry Liz, I'm so sorry.

1119
01:00:25,311 --> 01:00:27,624
Mike, the plane went down.

1120
01:00:28,901 --> 01:00:31,075
There were no survivors.

1121
01:00:31,973 --> 01:00:33,215
- No!

1122
01:00:33,250 --> 01:00:34,113
No, God!

1123
01:00:40,567 --> 01:00:41,430
Why?

1124
01:00:48,748 --> 01:00:52,787
[people talking from outside]

1125
01:01:03,142 --> 01:01:05,731
[car honking]

1126
01:01:06,663 --> 01:01:07,698
- Eddie.

1127
01:01:20,607 --> 01:01:21,470
- Mike.

1128
01:01:28,339 --> 01:01:29,409
- I'm glad you're here!

1129
01:01:29,444 --> 01:01:31,273
- I got here as fast as I could.

1130
01:01:31,308 --> 01:01:32,136
Is she?

1131
01:01:32,171 --> 01:01:32,999
- Go to her.

1132
01:01:33,034 --> 01:01:33,690
- You think?

1133
01:01:33,724 --> 01:01:35,588
- You're the perfect one.

1134
01:01:35,622 --> 01:01:37,555
Mike loved you so much.

1135
01:01:37,590 --> 01:01:38,729
- You're right.

1136
01:01:38,764 --> 01:01:41,318
Oh, this is a nightmare.

1137
01:01:41,352 --> 01:01:43,492
But, for Mike's sake.

1138
01:01:43,527 --> 01:01:44,908
- For hers too.

1139
01:02:00,026 --> 01:02:00,889
- Eddie.

1140
01:02:23,463 --> 01:02:25,465
You know what I figured out?

1141
01:02:26,639 --> 01:02:30,954
Mike and I were married 413 days exactly.

1142
01:02:32,887 --> 01:02:37,201
No one's ever gonna know
how much I loved that man.

1143
01:02:38,271 --> 01:02:39,031
- Me too.

1144
01:02:39,065 --> 01:02:41,102
- You did, didn't you?

1145
01:02:42,206 --> 01:02:44,761
- Did I ever tell you
about the time he said,

1146
01:02:44,795 --> 01:02:47,039
most boys dream of growing up to be

1147
01:02:47,073 --> 01:02:50,456
the president of the United States,

1148
01:02:50,490 --> 01:02:52,009
but not me, he said.

1149
01:02:52,044 --> 01:02:56,358
I dream of growing up and
marrying Elizabeth Taylor.

1150
01:02:59,258 --> 01:03:03,572
- Big, overdressed,
fatass broad. [laughing]

1151
01:03:06,058 --> 01:03:09,716
- You know, when we were
in Europe, Debbie and me,

1152
01:03:09,751 --> 01:03:12,202
and we ran into you and Mike,

1153
01:03:12,236 --> 01:03:15,550
I have to be honest, I was so envious.

1154
01:03:16,723 --> 01:03:17,863
- Of what?

1155
01:03:17,897 --> 01:03:20,072
Our brawls? [laughing]

1156
01:03:20,106 --> 01:03:20,762
- Yeah.

1157
01:03:20,797 --> 01:03:23,247
Yeah, you two were so close.

1158
01:03:26,457 --> 01:03:30,945
- I feel like half a pair
of scissors without him.

1159
01:03:34,707 --> 01:03:35,881
- I think,

1160
01:03:35,915 --> 01:03:39,885
Mike would want you to
get on with your life.

1161
01:03:52,759 --> 01:03:54,347
- Gonna invite me in?

1162
01:03:54,382 --> 01:03:56,902
- No, I'll come to you.

1163
01:03:56,936 --> 01:03:59,905
- I didn't get a chance to tell you, but,

1164
01:03:59,939 --> 01:04:03,149
the trouble with people
dying is, it's stupid.

1165
01:04:03,184 --> 01:04:05,703
- That's what Mike would have said.

1166
01:04:05,738 --> 01:04:07,360
Oh Richard, Mike's barely cold

1167
01:04:07,395 --> 01:04:10,398
and all they can think
about is their damn movie.

1168
01:04:10,432 --> 01:04:11,399
- This town.

1169
01:04:11,433 --> 01:04:14,885
I found things to shoot,
shooting around you.

1170
01:04:14,920 --> 01:04:15,886
Hey, kid.

1171
01:04:15,921 --> 01:04:18,855
I've been worried about you.

1172
01:04:18,889 --> 01:04:19,925
- Thanks.

1173
01:04:28,588 --> 01:04:29,589
[sighs] Oh, gosh.

1174
01:04:29,624 --> 01:04:33,939
I haven't been on this
lot since I was a child.

1175
01:04:33,973 --> 01:04:35,872
Went to school here.

1176
01:04:37,045 --> 01:04:39,703
I've given MGM my entire life.

1177
01:04:39,737 --> 01:04:42,119
And all they can say is,

1178
01:04:42,154 --> 01:04:45,882
all they want is to stuff me
back into the meat grinder.

1179
01:04:45,916 --> 01:04:47,711
- Hey, I'm with you on this.

1180
01:04:47,745 --> 01:04:48,988
We'll manage.

1181
01:04:50,817 --> 01:04:52,647
- They fired Judy.

1182
01:04:52,681 --> 01:04:54,476
Judy Garland, for God's sake!

1183
01:04:54,511 --> 01:04:58,204
Gable, Tracy, oh, and
they let Garbo sneak away

1184
01:04:58,239 --> 01:05:01,380
without so much as a thank you.

1185
01:05:01,414 --> 01:05:02,243
- Look.

1186
01:05:02,277 --> 01:05:04,590
I don't give a damn about this picture.

1187
01:05:04,624 --> 01:05:05,763
We'll recast.

1188
01:05:05,798 --> 01:05:07,351
You, please, go home.

1189
01:05:07,386 --> 01:05:10,699
It's a movie, for crying out loud!

1190
01:05:10,734 --> 01:05:14,876
- You're one of the few men
in this town who'd say that.

1191
01:05:14,911 --> 01:05:17,361
- Yeah, I'm a hell of a guy.

1192
01:05:24,644 --> 01:05:27,509
[emotional music]

1193
01:05:30,271 --> 01:05:34,516
- I think Mike would want
me to get back to work.

1194
01:05:34,551 --> 01:05:38,451
- Well, if that's what you
think Mike would have wanted.

1195
01:05:39,763 --> 01:05:43,905
- I came here today so you
would convince me to come back.

1196
01:05:43,940 --> 01:05:47,633
- No, you came here to convince yourself.

1197
01:05:47,667 --> 01:05:50,567
Now get your butt over to wardrobe.

1198
01:05:52,603 --> 01:05:54,364
[dogs barking]

1199
01:05:54,398 --> 01:05:56,573
[laughing]

1200
01:05:59,956 --> 01:06:01,819
- Hey, I got your message.

1201
01:06:01,854 --> 01:06:03,407
What's wrong?

1202
01:06:03,442 --> 01:06:04,339
- Oh no, nothing.

1203
01:06:04,374 --> 01:06:07,170
I wanted to give you something.

1204
01:06:11,105 --> 01:06:12,416
It was Mike's.

1205
01:06:16,834 --> 01:06:18,526
- His gold money clip?

1206
01:06:18,560 --> 01:06:20,010
Are you sure?

1207
01:06:20,045 --> 01:06:21,011
- Positive.

1208
01:06:21,046 --> 01:06:23,358
Mike loved you like a son.

1209
01:06:26,361 --> 01:06:27,224
Me too.

1210
01:06:32,850 --> 01:06:33,713
Sit down.

1211
01:06:35,992 --> 01:06:38,408
- I'd love it if you could come to Vegas,

1212
01:06:38,442 --> 01:06:41,894
to my opening at the Tropicana.

1213
01:06:41,928 --> 01:06:45,001
Or maybe that wouldn't
be such a good idea,

1214
01:06:45,035 --> 01:06:46,692
people might think...

1215
01:06:46,726 --> 01:06:48,625
- Not if Debbie's with you.

1216
01:06:48,659 --> 01:06:49,522
- She hates Vegas.

1217
01:06:49,557 --> 01:06:51,731
She can't stand the guys I hang out with,

1218
01:06:51,766 --> 01:06:53,423
she thinks I gamble too much.

1219
01:06:53,457 --> 01:06:54,631
- Well, you do.

1220
01:06:54,665 --> 01:06:56,702
[laughing]

1221
01:06:56,736 --> 01:06:57,565
- Yeah.

1222
01:06:57,599 --> 01:06:59,049
Is that a crime?

1223
01:06:59,084 --> 01:07:00,809
- Not in Vegas.

1224
01:07:00,844 --> 01:07:02,363
That's the charm.

1225
01:07:10,026 --> 01:07:12,200
Eddie, what do you want?

1226
01:07:13,339 --> 01:07:15,514
What do you really want?

1227
01:07:19,794 --> 01:07:21,037
- I want out.

1228
01:07:21,968 --> 01:07:24,419
- And what does Debbie want?

1229
01:07:26,387 --> 01:07:28,975
- She wants the marriage to work.

1230
01:07:29,010 --> 01:07:30,701
- That is a problem.

1231
01:07:31,426 --> 01:07:34,050
- I've got a bigger problem.

1232
01:07:35,016 --> 01:07:37,743
I think I'm falling in love with you.

1233
01:07:37,777 --> 01:07:39,365
I wanna marry you.

1234
01:07:43,473 --> 01:07:44,543
[popping]

1235
01:07:44,577 --> 01:07:46,786
[laughing]

1236
01:07:54,484 --> 01:07:55,623
- Fill her up.

1237
01:08:00,559 --> 01:08:03,286
[phone ringing]

1238
01:08:04,114 --> 01:08:05,150
Hello?

1239
01:08:12,088 --> 01:08:13,123
- Yeah?

1240
01:08:14,711 --> 01:08:16,092
Deb.

1241
01:08:16,126 --> 01:08:17,162
Debbie.

1242
01:08:18,232 --> 01:08:19,750
How did you know?

1243
01:08:21,994 --> 01:08:22,857
Oh.

1244
01:08:23,892 --> 01:08:26,274
Well that was a good guess.

1245
01:08:28,207 --> 01:08:29,864
Debbie, uh, listen.

1246
01:08:31,831 --> 01:08:33,281
This isn't easy.

1247
01:08:35,283 --> 01:08:39,149
Uh, Elizabeth and I are together here.

1248
01:08:39,184 --> 01:08:41,220
We're in love, Debbie.

1249
01:08:51,299 --> 01:08:52,887
- What did she say?

1250
01:08:54,095 --> 01:08:57,823
- She said, we'd discuss
it, just come home.

1251
01:09:03,139 --> 01:09:05,589
- Are you going home, Eddie?

1252
01:09:10,076 --> 01:09:11,733
- God, how could I?

1253
01:09:14,805 --> 01:09:17,877
- Frankly, I'm shocked
such lies would be printed.

1254
01:09:17,912 --> 01:09:19,983
Eddie and Liz are just good friends.

1255
01:09:20,017 --> 01:09:21,364
Now what's wrong with a good friend

1256
01:09:21,398 --> 01:09:23,297
taking another friend out for the evening.

1257
01:09:23,331 --> 01:09:26,162
- Debbie, you do that very well, but,

1258
01:09:26,196 --> 01:09:26,921
this is Hedda.

1259
01:09:26,955 --> 01:09:28,267
Level with me.

1260
01:09:28,302 --> 01:09:32,685
We both know Eddie is not
exactly mister picket fence.

1261
01:09:32,720 --> 01:09:34,722
What's really happening?

1262
01:09:37,449 --> 01:09:40,969
- All I'm saying, is Eddie's a great guy.

1263
01:09:43,903 --> 01:09:44,835
I love him.

1264
01:09:47,631 --> 01:09:49,219
Don't blame Eddie.

1265
01:09:50,669 --> 01:09:51,670
- Level with me.

1266
01:09:51,704 --> 01:09:53,499
I'll find out anyway.

1267
01:09:54,707 --> 01:09:57,227
The word is, that they are breaking up

1268
01:09:57,262 --> 01:09:59,056
and you are the cause.

1269
01:09:59,091 --> 01:10:00,230
- That's bull.

1270
01:10:00,265 --> 01:10:01,783
I don't break up marriages.

1271
01:10:01,818 --> 01:10:04,614
Besides, you don't break
up a happy marriage.

1272
01:10:04,648 --> 01:10:07,064
- You cannot hurt Debbie this way

1273
01:10:07,099 --> 01:10:09,274
without hurting yourself more.

1274
01:10:09,308 --> 01:10:12,277
Elizabeth, she truly loves Eddie.

1275
01:10:13,139 --> 01:10:15,314
- He doesn't love her, he never did.

1276
01:10:15,349 --> 01:10:16,798
The marriage was a farce.

1277
01:10:16,833 --> 01:10:19,939
- What do you think Mike
would think about all this?

1278
01:10:19,974 --> 01:10:21,734
- Mike's dead!

1279
01:10:21,769 --> 01:10:22,632
I'm alive.

1280
01:10:26,567 --> 01:10:30,260
What do you expect me to do, sleep alone?

1281
01:10:36,197 --> 01:10:37,992
[phone ringing]

1282
01:10:38,026 --> 01:10:39,476
You viper!

1283
01:10:39,511 --> 01:10:42,583
You depicted me as something
cruel and absolutely heartless!

1284
01:10:42,617 --> 01:10:45,241
- Darling, I only wrote what you told me.

1285
01:10:45,275 --> 01:10:47,864
- I didn't think you'd
print it, for God's sake!

1286
01:10:47,898 --> 01:10:49,866
- Darling, that's my job.

1287
01:10:49,900 --> 01:10:53,007
- You betrayed me, Aunt Hedda.

1288
01:10:53,041 --> 01:10:54,595
I will never forgive you.

1289
01:10:54,629 --> 01:10:58,909
- I would imagine Debbie's
singing the same song these days.

1290
01:11:01,947 --> 01:11:03,259
[crashing]

1291
01:11:03,293 --> 01:11:05,675
[clapping]

1292
01:11:06,538 --> 01:11:09,195
Eddie's ruined, of course.

1293
01:11:09,230 --> 01:11:12,509
Hate mail is flowing in like a flood

1294
01:11:12,544 --> 01:11:14,408
in the streets of this town.

1295
01:11:14,442 --> 01:11:16,686
The network's dropped him.

1296
01:11:16,720 --> 01:11:21,035
Only that element out in Las
Vegas will hire him any more.

1297
01:11:22,692 --> 01:11:25,729
The man does have a full-time job.

1298
01:11:26,765 --> 01:11:28,698
Full-time Elizabeth.

1299
01:11:28,732 --> 01:11:32,357
But then, you'd know all about
that, wouldn't you, Sarah?

1300
01:11:32,391 --> 01:11:36,430
- I won't say a bad word about Elizabeth.

1301
01:11:36,464 --> 01:11:38,328
But if she had listened to me,

1302
01:11:38,363 --> 01:11:40,123
this never would have happened.

1303
01:11:40,157 --> 01:11:43,713
That Fisher man has taken her
off to Europe for a honeymoon.

1304
01:11:43,747 --> 01:11:47,579
Elizabeth says she
hopes it lasts 40 years.

1305
01:11:48,856 --> 01:11:49,926
- Poor Eddie.

1306
01:11:56,760 --> 01:11:59,418
[speaking in foreign language]

1307
01:11:59,453 --> 01:12:01,006
- Do you speak English?

1308
01:12:01,040 --> 01:12:05,182
No that's okay, that's
okay, just put it down.

1309
01:12:05,217 --> 01:12:08,393
Very good, very good, that's fine.

1310
01:12:08,427 --> 01:12:11,154
This can go downstairs in storage.

1311
01:12:11,188 --> 01:12:15,123
[speaking in foreign language]

1312
01:12:18,368 --> 01:12:21,060
- Could you order me up a scotch?

1313
01:12:21,095 --> 01:12:22,614
- In a sec, babe.

1314
01:12:26,238 --> 01:12:28,033
[phone ringing]

1315
01:12:28,067 --> 01:12:32,037
- Really, I'm in so much
pain, my back again.

1316
01:12:35,040 --> 01:12:37,525
Are you going to answer that?

1317
01:12:46,292 --> 01:12:48,329
What in God's heaven is this?

1318
01:12:48,364 --> 01:12:49,123
- Oh, it's fine.

1319
01:12:49,157 --> 01:12:50,331
Just medicine.

1320
01:12:50,366 --> 01:12:52,333
Don't worry, it's all
been prescribed for me

1321
01:12:52,368 --> 01:12:53,921
by Dr. Jacobson in New York.

1322
01:12:53,955 --> 01:12:56,475
- Oh Eddie, don't you read the magazines?

1323
01:12:56,510 --> 01:12:57,925
That's Dr. Feelgood!

1324
01:12:57,959 --> 01:12:59,444
He's notorious!

1325
01:12:59,478 --> 01:13:03,206
- It's just vitamins, and
a bunch of other stuff.

1326
01:13:03,240 --> 01:13:04,069
- Stuff?

1327
01:13:04,103 --> 01:13:05,277
Damn right, stuff.

1328
01:13:05,311 --> 01:13:07,244
Stuff mixed with amphetamines.

