and that picture's got
to be Butterfield 8.

1377
01:15:20,136 --> 01:15:21,240
- That is outrageous!

1378
01:15:21,275 --> 01:15:23,173
- I'm afraid it means that
you're gonna have to do

1379
01:15:23,208 --> 01:15:26,591
Butterfield 8 for considerable
less compensation.

1380
01:15:26,625 --> 01:15:28,627
- You're asking me to play a whore.

1381
01:15:28,662 --> 01:15:31,043
- That word does not
appear in our screenplay.

1382
01:15:31,078 --> 01:15:33,632
And I want to remind
you that Butterfield 8

1383
01:15:33,667 --> 01:15:36,152
is a bestselling novel by a renowned

1384
01:15:36,186 --> 01:15:38,361
and respected American author.

1385
01:15:38,395 --> 01:15:39,500
- I don't care!

1386
01:15:39,535 --> 01:15:42,192
I won't do it, under any circumstance.

1387
01:15:42,227 --> 01:15:45,886
- Well, if you refuse to abide
by the terms of our contract,

1388
01:15:45,920 --> 01:15:48,958
I'm afraid it leaves us
no choice but to block you

1389
01:15:48,992 --> 01:15:51,961
from working anywhere
for the next two years.

1390
01:15:51,995 --> 01:15:55,758
- And this is how you choose
to end an 18-year relationship.

1391
01:15:55,792 --> 01:16:00,417
- Liz, sentiment went out
of this business years ago.

1392
01:16:00,452 --> 01:16:02,178
Adjust! I've had to.

1393
01:16:02,212 --> 01:16:03,835
Oh yes, but that's the business.

1394
01:16:03,869 --> 01:16:07,010
Personally, me, I'm still
a very sentimental guy.

1395
01:16:07,045 --> 01:16:09,875
I remember the luck we
made with National Velvet,

1396
