Let me walk, I'm better walking.

1461
01:19:40,845 --> 01:19:42,536
I'm sick of opening that door every day

1462
01:19:42,570 --> 01:19:45,435
and finding you boozed
out, burned up, and ugly.

1463
01:19:45,470 --> 01:19:47,852
Boozed out, burned up, and ugly.

1464
01:19:47,886 --> 01:19:49,198
I'm sick of...

1465
01:19:55,825 --> 01:19:58,414
[dog barking]

1466
01:20:41,975 --> 01:20:44,287
- God, not more hate mail.

1467
01:20:44,322 --> 01:20:48,360
- Fox is on my back about
delays on Cleopatra.

1468
01:20:49,120 --> 01:20:51,294
They're way over budget.

1469
01:20:53,710 --> 01:20:54,573
Baby?

1470
01:20:57,128 --> 01:20:57,922
- What?

1471
01:20:57,956 --> 01:20:59,337
I'm sick, okay?

1472
01:21:01,615 --> 01:21:04,860
- I don't know how much
of this I can take.

1473
01:21:04,894 --> 01:21:06,344
- What about me?

1474
01:21:07,103 --> 01:21:09,347
- Everything is stalled here.

1475
01:21:09,381 --> 01:21:11,004
I have no career!

1476
01:21:11,038 --> 01:21:12,798
You're too sick to work.

1477
01:21:12,833 --> 01:21:13,799
Even if you could,

1478
01:21:13,834 --> 01:21:16,043
the rain won't stop.
[coughing]

1479
01:21:16,078 --> 01:21:19,875
This town is like living in
the bottom of a damn well.

1480
01:21:19,909 --> 01:21:21,738
- I hate it too, Eddie.

1481
01:21:21,773 --> 01:21:23,154
- Maybe I should go back

1482
01:21:23,188 --> 01:21:25,535
and try and get some work, something.

1483
01:21:25,570 --> 01:21:26,985
- Now don't start that again.

1484
01:21:27,020 --> 01:21:30,195
- I said I'm just thinking about it.

1485
01:21:31,403 --> 01:21:34,510
- I'll tell you what I think about.

1486
01:21:43,174 --> 01:21:46,349
Every man I've ever known has either

1487
01:21:48,075 --> 01:21:50,043
died or abandoned me.

1488
01:21:58,810 --> 01:22:01,054
[crying]

1489
01:22:04,816 --> 01:22:07,681
[dramatic music]

1490
01:22:17,622 --> 01:22:19,313
- Oh my God.

1491
01:22:19,348 --> 01:22:20,728
Help!

1492
01:22:20,763 --> 01:22:22,006
Someone help!

1493
01:22:23,421 --> 01:22:25,561
[gasping]

1494
01:22:30,911 --> 01:22:31,877
What is it?

1495
01:22:31,912 --> 01:22:32,878
- Congestion.

1496
01:22:32,913 --> 01:22:35,226
She's not getting any air.

1497
01:22:53,830 --> 01:22:55,901
- Can you believe this?

1498
01:22:55,936 --> 01:22:58,249
Tons of letters and telegrams.

1499
01:22:58,283 --> 01:23:01,459
And look here, here's your obituary.

1500
01:23:02,356 --> 01:23:03,185
- I saw.

1501
01:23:05,014 --> 01:23:06,982
- Everyone loves you.

1502
01:23:08,086 --> 01:23:10,330
- Everyone loves me dead.

1503
01:23:11,400 --> 01:23:14,920
Alive, I'm the whore of Babylon.

1504
01:23:14,955 --> 01:23:16,405
- No babe, they love you.

1505
01:23:16,439 --> 01:23:19,753
The fans, they forgive you everything.

1506
01:23:21,237 --> 01:23:23,377
- I'll let them know when I have.

1507
01:23:23,412 --> 01:23:26,587
- Now is that any way to get better?

1508
01:23:29,487 --> 01:23:31,696
[knocking]

1509
01:23:35,907 --> 01:23:36,735
- Mummy.

1510
01:23:36,770 --> 01:23:38,427
I've missed you so.

1511
01:23:39,945 --> 01:23:40,808
Daddy.

1512
01:23:48,954 --> 01:23:49,783
Mummy.

1513
01:23:49,817 --> 01:23:51,405
I saw Mike, I did.

1514
01:23:52,544 --> 01:23:53,338
- Where, baby?

1515
01:23:53,373 --> 01:23:55,616
- When I died, I saw him.

1516
01:24:00,414 --> 01:24:03,383
I wanted so badly to be with him.

1517
01:24:04,867 --> 01:24:06,248
But he said no.

1518
01:24:07,835 --> 01:24:09,147
No, you can't.

1519
01:24:10,079 --> 01:24:11,736
It's not your time.

1520
01:24:13,703 --> 01:24:14,566
Go back.

1521
01:24:16,016 --> 01:24:17,052
Back.

1522
01:24:18,777 --> 01:24:20,365
- Did he, darling?

1523
01:24:22,609 --> 01:24:24,266
- Fight to go back.

1524
01:24:25,750 --> 01:24:27,476
That's what he said.

1525
01:24:28,925 --> 01:24:30,651
I'll be here.

1526
01:24:30,686 --> 01:24:31,756
He said that.

1527
01:24:32,791 --> 01:24:33,861
I'll be here.

1528
01:24:37,002 --> 01:24:39,867
[people chanting]

1529
01:24:42,077 --> 01:24:44,286
- Can you hear that, hun?

1530
01:24:45,045 --> 01:24:47,703
Would you get a load of that?

1531
01:24:47,737 --> 01:24:50,602
[people cheering]

1532
01:25:03,443 --> 01:25:05,410
- Burt Lancaster wins his Oscar

1533
01:25:05,445 --> 01:25:09,034
against an outstanding
field of movie favorites.

1534
01:25:09,069 --> 01:25:11,485
The distinguished audience is hushed.

1535
01:25:11,520 --> 01:25:13,729
The tension is great when to Yul Brynner

1536
01:25:13,763 --> 01:25:18,251
falls the assignment of
telling who is Best Actress.

1537
01:25:19,079 --> 01:25:20,563
- Elizabeth Taylor.

1538
01:25:20,598 --> 01:25:21,633
[clapping]

1539
01:25:21,668 --> 01:25:23,980
- Escorted by her husband, Eddie Fisher,

1540
01:25:24,015 --> 01:25:26,431
the star who was honored for her portrayal

1541
01:25:26,466 --> 01:25:30,470
in MGM's Butterfield 8 comes
up to receive the Oscar.

1542
01:25:30,504 --> 01:25:34,094
A pleasure indeed, for Elizabeth
Taylor has won a victory

1543
01:25:34,129 --> 01:25:36,924
over a near-fatal illness.

1544
01:25:36,959 --> 01:25:39,272
And this too is her fourth consecutive try

1545
01:25:39,306 --> 01:25:40,894
at winning an Oscar.

1546
01:25:40,928 --> 01:25:42,999
And now it is hers at last.

1547
01:25:43,034 --> 01:25:47,521
She is overcome with emotion
as the presentation is made.

1548
01:25:55,633 --> 01:25:56,461
- Oh.

1549
01:25:58,670 --> 01:26:00,327
I don't really know

1550
01:26:01,156 --> 01:26:03,537
how to express my gratitude

1551
01:26:04,262 --> 01:26:06,920
for this after everything.

1552
01:26:06,954 --> 01:26:10,372
I guess all I can do is say thank you.

1553
01:26:10,406 --> 01:26:12,926
Thank you, with all my heart.

1554
01:26:14,790 --> 01:26:16,654
[clapping]

1555
01:26:16,688 --> 01:26:19,967
- Academy Awards, a reminder
that every moviegoer

1556
01:26:20,002 --> 01:26:21,797
is also a star maker.

1557
01:26:27,837 --> 01:26:29,322
- Butterfield 8.

1558
01:26:29,356 --> 01:26:31,255
- Congratulations.

1559
01:26:31,289 --> 01:26:33,395
I'm so happy for you.

1560
01:26:33,429 --> 01:26:37,192
Now, would you like some more good news?

1561
01:26:37,226 --> 01:26:38,400
- Yes.

1562
01:26:38,434 --> 01:26:40,298
- We're gonna start up
again with Cleopatra.

1563
01:26:40,333 --> 01:26:42,058
Only this time we're going to Rome.

1564
01:26:42,093 --> 01:26:44,440
We're going to pretend that Rome is Rome.

1565
01:26:44,475 --> 01:26:48,030
And here's the kicker, Joe
Mankiewicz said he would direct.

1566
01:26:48,064 --> 01:26:50,170
- Oh Walter, that's wonderful.

1567
01:26:50,205 --> 01:26:52,103
- But he wants to recast the men.

1568
01:26:52,137 --> 01:26:54,519
Only English actors, the cream.

1569
01:26:54,554 --> 01:26:56,832
- Rex Harrison, of course.

1570
01:26:56,866 --> 01:26:57,971
- For Caesar, yes.

1571
01:26:58,005 --> 01:27:00,145
A real actor, a man of the field.

1572
01:27:00,180 --> 01:27:02,907
- And Antony, who will play Antony?

1573
01:27:02,941 --> 01:27:04,357
- You're gonna love this.

1574
01:27:04,391 --> 01:27:06,669
The best, the new Olivier.

1575
01:27:06,704 --> 01:27:08,223
- Who?

1576
01:27:08,257 --> 01:27:09,776
- Richard Burton.

1577
01:27:11,502 --> 01:27:12,365
- Who?

1578
01:27:13,193 --> 01:27:16,990
[dramatic orchestral music]

1579
01:27:54,959 --> 01:27:56,029
- Hmm, what's that line again?

1580
01:27:56,063 --> 01:27:57,030
- I need to--

1581
01:27:57,064 --> 01:27:57,893
- Heard it.

1582
01:27:57,927 --> 01:28:00,654
[group murmurs]

1583
01:28:02,104 --> 01:28:05,107
[water pours]

1584
01:28:05,141 --> 01:28:06,073
- Please, will you stop fiddling.

1585
01:28:06,108 --> 01:28:07,696
- I'm trying to fix it, Mr Burton.

1586
01:28:07,730 --> 01:28:09,249
- Ah hail,

1587
01:28:09,284 --> 01:28:10,215
Encuador!

1588
01:28:10,250 --> 01:28:11,734
- What's in the cup, Richard?

1589
