1905
01:40:35,891 --> 01:40:36,892
- Yes, I think so.

1906
01:40:36,927 --> 01:40:37,755
- Would it?

1907
01:40:37,790 --> 01:40:38,618
- Yes.
- Oh.

1908
01:40:38,653 --> 01:40:39,481
[laughs]

1909
01:40:39,516 --> 01:40:41,035
What a pity.

1910
01:40:41,069 --> 01:40:44,176
- I've come too far for that.

1911
01:40:44,210 --> 01:40:46,178
- And how far have you come?

1912
01:40:46,212 --> 01:40:48,283
- Too, too far.

1913
01:40:48,318 --> 01:40:51,010
[laughs]

1914
01:40:51,045 --> 01:40:52,667
You know, Richard, silly as it sounds,

1915
01:40:52,701 --> 01:40:55,256
I can't remember a time
when I wasn't famous.

1916
01:40:55,290 --> 01:40:58,742
And that hasn't left much
time for anything else.

1917
01:40:58,776 --> 01:40:59,950
- Such as?

1918
01:40:59,984 --> 01:41:01,227
- Well, love.

1919
01:41:02,021 --> 01:41:03,471
I mean, when I was a child,

1920
01:41:03,505 --> 01:41:05,335
I never felt like I could get enough love,

1921
01:41:05,369 --> 01:41:07,785
