Here, you know what they would do?

2052
01:46:39,531 --> 01:46:41,015
Hell, they would stand
up and they'd applaud!

2053
01:46:41,049 --> 01:46:42,154
They would have a parade!

2054
01:46:42,188 --> 01:46:43,017
- Eddie, listen.

2055
01:46:43,051 --> 01:46:44,570
Please stay here.

2056
01:46:45,778 --> 01:46:46,710
I need you.

2057
01:46:48,229 --> 01:46:49,403
Please stay.

2058
01:46:52,267 --> 01:46:55,478
[knock on door]

2059
01:46:55,512 --> 01:46:56,651
- Ah, good evening Sir,

2060
01:46:56,686 --> 01:46:58,895
did you know that the verb, to be,

2061
01:46:58,929 --> 01:47:01,863
is the most brilliant verb
in the English language?

2062
01:47:01,898 --> 01:47:03,796
I am ...

2063
01:47:03,831 --> 01:47:05,108
You are!

2064
01:47:05,142 --> 01:47:06,005
We are!

2065
01:47:07,835 --> 01:47:09,733
Yeah, [laughs].

2066
01:47:09,768 --> 01:47:10,631
They are!

2067
01:47:11,908 --> 01:47:13,081
- It's Richard.

2068
01:47:13,116 --> 01:47:14,082
- I see.

2069
01:47:14,117 --> 01:47:15,187
[laughs]

2070
01:47:15,221 --> 01:47:16,947
